3. cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper describes a compiler for logic programs, which is relevant to the subfield of programming languages. 
4. cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper may be relevant to natural language processing, as preferences can be expressed in natural language and incorporated into logic programs. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): While not directly related to data structures and algorithms, the paper may be of interest to researchers in this subfield who are interested in logic programming and its applications.
